  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "It'd be nice if we could provide our behavior tests (e.g. [`Ownable`](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/blob/release-v1.11.0/test/ownership/Ownable.behaviour.js)) to users, so that they could in turn check that contracts inhering from those still preserve the base behavior (if applicable) and that it hasn't been accidentally broken (e.g. by overriding a modifier, etc.).\r\n\r\nRelated to #326.",
